The "'''State Bureau of Child and Animal Protection'''" was the name assigned to Child Protective Services in a number of states during the early 20th century. This was all part of "The Humane Movement" documented by the [https://books.google.com/books?id=Jo7obsJ3TJsC&pg=PA216&lpg=PA216&dq=Bureau+of+Child+and+Animal+Protection&source=bl&ots=mkfNe9Lzg5&sig=uXVBKCL_bHKGyvFu9y-Xp5t9lyI&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjf3_fsjIjVAhVK3IMKHWXaA6YQ6AEIVTAJ#v=onepage&q=Bureau%20of%20Child%20and%20Animal%20Protection&f=false Descriptive Survey] by the same name.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Jo7obsJ3TJsC&pg=PA216&lpg=PA216&dq=Bureau+of+Child+and+Animal+Protection&source=bl&ots=mkfNe9Lzg5&sig=uXVBKCL_bHKGyvFu9y-Xp5t9lyI&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjf3_fsjIjVAhVK3IMKHWXaA6YQ6AEIVTAJ#v=onepage&q=Bureau%20of%20Child%20and%20Animal%20Protection&f=false|title=The Humane Movement: A Descriptive Survey, Prepared on the Henry Bergh Foundation for the Promotion of Humane Education in Columbia University|last=McCrea|first=Roswell Cheney|date=1910|publisher=Columbia University Press|language=en}}</ref> The marriage of Child and Animal Protections was documented in the same survey showing Colorado as a champion of this philosophy 

== State Bureaus ==

We know of at least 3 states that used this name: Colorado<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=j4tPAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA1432&lpg=PA1432&dq=Bureau+of+Child+and+Animal+Protection+constitutional&source=bl&ots=Qv1Dj6SEH-&sig=acgTL4qXG7ZGWR9OLMK2mpjqvf8&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjh_K2UjojVAhUMw4MKHSkHDlAQ6AEINjAD#v=onepage&q=Bureau%20of%20Child%20and%20Animal%20Protection%20constitutional&f=false|title=The Revised Statutes of Colorado, 1908: Containing the Declaration of Independence, the Constitution of the United States of America, the Enabling Act, the Constitution of the State of Colorado, the Code of Civil Procedure, and All General Laws of the State of Colorado : Authorized by the Sixteenth General Assembly|date=1908|publisher=Col., Printed by the Smith-Brooks printing Company|language=en}}</ref>, Montana<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/reportofbureauof1904mont|title=Report of the Bureau of Child and Animal Protection, State of Montana|last=Montana. Bureau of Child and Animal Protection|date=1904|publisher=Helena, Mont. : Independent Pub. Co.|others=Montana State Library}}</ref> and Texas<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=2RkyAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA6&lpg=PA6&dq=Bureau+of+Child+and+Animal+Protection&source=bl&ots=9sjyskpBYd&sig=I8pQdvqeeOYwSdQN4WHmw78b8Zc&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjf3_fsjIjVAhVK3IMKHWXaA6YQ6AEIUjAI#v=onepage&q=Bureau%20of%20Child%20and%20Animal%20Protection&f=false|title=Biennial Report of the Texas Bureau of Child and Animal Protection July 1, 1913 to January 1, 1915|last=Protection|first=Texas Bureau of Child and Animal|date=1915|publisher=Von Boeckmann-Jones Company, printers|language=en}}</ref>. 

