'''Sunflower Revolution''' is a 3-day event held every fall in [[Cincinnati, Ohio]], that raises funds and awareness about [[Parkinson's Disease]]. The event is sponsored by the James J. and Joan A. Gardner Center for Parkinson's Disease and Movement Disorders at the University of Cincinnati Neuroscience Institute, a part of UC Health [[University of Cincinnati]].<ref>{{cite news | last = | first = | coauthors = | title =Phinney To Headline Fund-Raiser | newspaper =The Cincinnati Post | location =Cincinnati, OH | pages = | language = | publisher = | date =22 June 2007 | url =http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-165619409.html | accessdate =21 May 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last = | first = | authorlink = | coauthors = | title =Sunflower Revolution Funds Parkinson’s Projects | work = | publisher =U of C Health News | date =19 December 2008 | url =http://healthnews.uc.edu/news/?/7902/ | format = | doi = | accessdate =21 May 2013}}</ref>
