The '''World Council of Optometry''' ('''WCO''') is a membership organization for the development of [[optometry]] ([[eye care]]) internationally.<ref name="who">{{cite web| url=http://www.who.int/workforcealliance/members_partners/member_list/wcoptometry/en/ | title=The World Council of Optometry (WCO) | publisher=[[World Health Organization]] | accessdate=11 November 2015 }}</ref>
The WCO is the first and only optometric organization to have official relations with the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO).<ref name="who" /> It represents 250,000 optometrists from 75 member organizations in over 40 countries.<ref name="iapb">{{cite web| url=http://www.iapb.org/member/world-council-optometry | title=World Council of Optometry | publisher=International Agency for the Prevention of Blindness | accessdate=11 November 2015 }}</ref> The WCO organizes the World Congress of Optometry.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://worldcongressofoptometry.org/ | title=World Congress of Optometry | publisher=World Council of Optometry | accessdate=11 November 2015 }}</ref>
In 2015, the WCO relocated to the [[American Optometric Association]] (AOA) headquarters in [[St Louis]], [[Missouri]], United States.<ref name="aoa">{{cite web| url=http://www.aoa.org/newsroom/american-optometric-association-announces--world-council-of-optometry-relocating-its-headquarters-to-st-louis?sso=y | title=World Council of Optometry Relocating to American Optometric Association Headquarters in St. Louis | publisher=[[American Optometric Association]] | date=20 May 2015 | accessdate=11 November 2015 }}</ref>
